You posted something about vulgarity and a blue collar worker with a ninth grade education or something?<br>
<br>
I have to take offense at that. My grandfather, GOD rest his soul, was a blue collar hard working man.  He did not use profanity. In fact, if my brother swore, Grandpa would take his hand away from his bottle of Wild Turkry just long enough to smack my brother out of his chair.<br>
<br>
After that exertion, he would hear no more vocabulary, and would be able to drift off to a nice sleep -- while his cigarette burnt another black line on the pine kitchen table.<br>
<br>
Two things I cannot figure out about my Grandpa though.  One is how he could have a dead bird on his bumper no less than 4 or 5 times a month.  Other is, how he could have kept my Grandma in a new Caddy every two years and ended up owning several gas stations around the Buffalo, New York area.<br>
<br>
:::shrug:::<br>
<br>
Hard work I guess...<br>
